.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
manages a collection of transient text buffers ("scratchpads") with
persistent history, full-text search, and shell integration.
It stores all data in a SQLite database owned by a background daemon
and exposes operations through both a CLI and a TUI.
.Pp
Bold text is used to denote commands and flags, and emphasis for file paths.
.Pp
On first invocation,
.Nm
automatically starts the daemon if it is not already running.
The daemon listens on a Unix domain socket
.Pq Pa $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tmpbuffer.sock
and serialises all writes to the SQLite database, ensuring consistency
between concurrent CLI and TUI sessions.
