.It Xo
.Ic edit
.Op Fl -editor Ar cmd
.Ar id
.Xc
Open a buffer in an external editor.
The daemon writes the buffer content to a temporary file, launches
the editor, and waits for it to exit. On exit, the modified content
is read back and persisted.
.Pp
If the editor exits with a non-zero code, the user is prompted whether
to keep or discard the changes.
.Bl -tag -width "-editor"
