.It Xo
.Ic rm
.Op Fl -permanent
.Ar id
.Xc
Delete a buffer.
By default the buffer is moved to the trash (soft delete), where it
remains for a configurable retention period before being permanently
removed.
.Bl -tag -width "-permanent"
.It Fl -permanent , Fl P
Skip the trash and remove the buffer immediately.
.El
