This flag is required.
.It Fl -new , Fl n
Create a new buffer with the command output instead of replacing the
original buffer's content. The new buffer inherits the original label
with " (piped)" appended.
.El
.Pp
If the command exits non-zero or produces no output, an error is
displayed and the buffer is not modified.
